apy().details: Adapter returns APR scaled by 1e18. Convert to bps by / 1e14

params._sToken: S token address (what the vault holds)
params._stsAdapter: Adapter for converting S to stS

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

GAUGE().notice: Gauge where we stake LP tokens to earn rewards

POOL().notice: SwapX pool where we provide S/stS liquidity

STS().notice: Adapter for converting S to stS tokens and back

SWAPX().notice: Adapter for working with SwapX pools and gauges

apy().notice: Get current yield percentage in basis points (1% = 100 bps)

components().notice: Return component list for off-chain introspection

deposit(uint256).notice: Deposit S tokens into strategy. Converts half to stS,         adds both to SwapX pool, stakes the LP tokens

harvest().notice: Collect rewards from SwapX gauge and keep them as free S.         Assumes rewards are S tokens or equivalent. If rewards are different         tokens, this function should be extended to swap them

stakedLp().notice: How many LP tokens we have staked in the gauge

totalAssets().notice: Calculate total value in S terms. This conservative version         only counts free S balance. Doesn't include LP or stS value since         that needs price oracles. Could be improved to include LP/stS valuation

withdraw(uint256).notice: Withdraw S back to vault. If we don't have enough free S,         unstakes LP and exits SwapX pool. Converts any stS back to S.         Extra tokens stay in strategy for next time
